ntrepreneurship Centers in Atlanta, Broward County, Chicago, Los Angeles, Palm Beach County and Philadelphia. Technical assistance programming includes workshops, trainings, bootcamps, and one on one counseling sessions offered to small business owners (as defined by the SBA).</p><p style=''text-align: justify''><span style=''color:black;''>By participating in the grant application process, each Applicant hereby attests that:</span></p><ui><li style=''list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;text-indent: -1.3em;padding-left: 1em;text-align: justify;''> All information provided, including all required documents to be submitted by Applicant during the application process and through the grant portal are accurate and complete, including “Borrower Details” and “Business Entity” information.</li><li style=''list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;text-indent: -1.3em;padding-left: 1em;text-align: justify;''>The grant proceeds will be used as described on the “Funding Application” page under “Purpose”.</li><li style=''list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;text-indent: -1.3em;padding-left: 1em;text-align: justify;''>It is a client of an Urban League affiliate Entrepreneurship Center program and has received or is receiving professional services or technical assistance from such NUL Affiliate.</li><li style=''list-style-type: disc;list-style-position: inside;text-indent: -1.3em;padding-left: 1em;text-align: justify;''>It will complete and submit the National Urban League Photo Release Form through which the Applicant consents to the use by the National Urban League, its affiliates and its designees and partners, of the business and business owner’s names, photographs, likeness, biography, voice, performance and/or video for advertising and promotional purposes in any and all media now or hereafter known, worldwide and without limitation and without additional compensation, notification or permission, except where prohibited by law.</li><li styl